President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Preeta D. Bansal and Boris Bershteyn to key administration posts. Bansal served as the General Counsel and Senior Policy Advisor for the Office of Management and Budget from 2009 to 2011 and was a government member of the Council of the Administrative Conference of the United States. She has a background in law and has held various positions, including Solicitor General of the State of New York. Bershteyn currently serves as the General Counsel of the Office of Management and Budget and has previously worked as Special Assistant to the President and Associate White House Counsel. He also has a background in law and has worked at law firms and served as a Law Clerk for Justice David H. Souter of the U.S. Supreme Court.